        "new_string": "## BUG IDENTIFIED (CONFIRMED)\n\n**Root Cause:** Software state flags (`single_cmd` and `polling_mode`) are not reset during hardware reset on resume\n\n**Execution Flow:**\n1. Timeout occurs \u2192 azx_rirb_get_response (line 951) sets `chip->single_cmd = 1`\n2. Suspend \u2192 azx_suspend calls azx_stop_chip which sets `chip->initialized = 0` (line 2448)\n3. BUT `chip->single_cmd` remains 1 (not reset in azx_stop_chip)\n4. Resume \u2192 azx_init_chip (line 2561) is called\n5. azx_init_chip checks `if (!chip->single_cmd)` before calling azx_init_cmd_io (line 1222)\n6. Since `single_cmd = 1`, CORB/RIRB initialization is SKIPPED\n7. Result: Hardware reset but driver stuck in single_cmd mode \u2192 codec communication fails\n\n**Fix Location:** `sound/pci/hda/hda_intel.c`, function `azx_init_chip`, after line 1215\n\n**Required Change:** Reset flags immediately after azx_reset:\n- `chip->single_cmd = 0;`\n- `chip->polling_mode = 0;`\n- `chip->poll_count = 0;`\n\nThis ensures after hardware reset, driver returns to normal CORB/RIRB mode",
